1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,366
我先问你一件事
Let me ask you something first

2
00:00:01,566 --> 00:00:03,100
你上一次换手机
The last time you got a new phone

3
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:04,200
花了多少钱
How much did you spend

4
00:00:04,366 --> 00:00:05,466
8000
8000

5
00:00:05,466 --> 00:00:06,300
10000
10000

6
00:00:06,433 --> 00:00:07,900
还是12000
Or 12000

7
00:00:08,166 --> 00:00:09,400
你有没有想过
Have you ever wondered

8
00:00:09,566 --> 00:00:12,266
10年前最贵的iPhone才5288
10 years ago the most expensive iPhone was only 5288

9
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:15,400
现在ProMax1TB
Now a ProMax 1TB

10
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,166
13999
13999

11
00:00:17,466 --> 00:00:19,000
价格翻了快3倍
The price nearly tripled

12
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:20,300
但你这10年
But in these 10 years

13
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,666
工资涨了几倍
How many times has your salary gone up

14
00:00:21,866 --> 00:00:23,000
更怪的是
What's even weirder

15
00:00:23,466 --> 00:00:24,266
越贵
The more expensive

16
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:25,400
越多人抢
The more people fight for it

17
00:00:25,566 --> 00:00:27,400
苹果2024年财报
Apple's 2024 financial report

18
00:00:27,466 --> 00:00:29,366
iPhone卖出23亿台
iPhone sold 230 million units

19
00:00:29,366 --> 00:00:31,166
Pro系列占一半以上
Pro series accounted for over half

20
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,500
你是不是也这样过
Have you been like this too

21
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,466
预算本来8000
Your budget was 8000 to begin with

22
00:00:34,466 --> 00:00:36,766
到了店里咬咬牙加2000买Pro
Then at the store you grit your teeth and added 2000 for the Pro

23
00:00:37,266 --> 00:00:38,333
反正都买了
Might as well go all in

24
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:39,900
这不是你一个人
You're not the only one

25
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,100
真相是
The truth is

26
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,533
一部手机为什么越来越贵
Why phones keep getting more expensive

27
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:45,633
跟成本几乎没关系
Has almost nothing to do with cost

28
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,133
跟你的脑子有关系
It has everything to do with your brain

29
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,900
今天我用10分钟
Today I'll use 10 minutes

30
00:00:49,066 --> 00:00:53,200
告诉你手机变贵背后的3个经济学陷阱
To tell you about the 3 economic traps behind rising phone prices

31
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,200
搞懂它
Understand them

32
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,800
你下次买手机至少能少花3000块
And you'll save at least 3000 on your next phone

33
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:58,533
而且这3个陷阱
And these 3 traps

34
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,066
不只在手机店
Aren't just at the phone store

35
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:01,300
你买车
When you buy a car

36
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:02,300
买包
Buy a bag

37
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:03,166
买电脑
Buy a computer

38
00:01:03,166 --> 00:01:04,166
报培训班
Sign up for a training course

39
00:01:04,466 --> 00:01:05,500
全在踩
You're falling for all of them

40
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:06,800
你想想这个画面
Picture this scene

41
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:08,100
你坐地铁
You're on the subway

42
00:01:08,366 --> 00:01:11,700
对面那个人掏出一台折叠的MateXT
The person across from you pulls out a foldable MateXT

43
00:01:11,866 --> 00:01:14,000
你5000块的iPhone拿手里
And your 5000-yuan iPhone in hand

44
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:15,966
都觉得有点寒酸
Suddenly feels a bit embarrassing

45
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:16,933
注意听
Pay attention

46
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,900
这种感觉不是你矫情
This feeling isn't you being overly sensitive

47
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:22,466
是经济学家研究了100多年的一个规律
It's a pattern economists have studied for over 100 years

48
00:01:22,666 --> 00:01:24,033
1899年
In 1899

49
00:01:24,033 --> 00:01:26,600
美国经济学家凡勃伦写了一本书
American economist Veblen wrote a book

50
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,400
叫有闲阶级论
Called The Theory of the Leisure Class

51
00:01:28,466 --> 00:01:30,333
他发现一个反常识的现象
He discovered a counterintuitive phenomenon

52
00:01:30,366 --> 00:01:31,300
有些东西
Some things

53
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:32,700
价格越贵
The higher the price

54
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:34,166
买的人反而越多
The more people want to buy them

55
00:01:34,266 --> 00:01:35,966
按经济学常识
According to basic economics

56
00:01:35,966 --> 00:01:37,666
一个商品涨价10%
When a product's price goes up 10%

57
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,733
需求至少跌5%
Demand should drop at least 5%

58
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,066
但有些东西反过来
But some things work the other way

59
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:43,966
涨价30%
Price goes up 30%

60
00:01:44,266 --> 00:01:45,366
销量涨50%
Sales go up 50%

61
00:01:45,866 --> 00:01:47,966
这后来被叫做凡勃伦效应
This later became known as the Veblen effect

62
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:48,833
劳力士
Rolex

63
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:49,700
爱马仕
Hermes

64
00:01:49,766 --> 00:01:50,966
奔驰大G
Mercedes G-Wagon

65
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:52,466
都是这一类
All fall into this category

66
00:01:52,633 --> 00:01:54,266
你猜苹果是不是
Guess if Apple is one too

67
00:01:54,433 --> 00:01:55,233
是
It is

68
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,766
从乔布斯起就是
Since Jobs it's always been

69
00:01:58,266 --> 00:02:01,533
2007年第一代iPhone卖499美元
In 2007 the first iPhone sold for 499 dollars

70
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:04,533
当时诺基亚最贵的型号也就300美元
Back then Nokia's most expensive model was only 300 dollars

71
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:08,300
苹果一上来就把自己定在一个高出别人一档的位置
Apple positioned itself a full tier above everyone else right from the start

72
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,300
之后每一代都涨
Every generation after that went up

73
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,100
iPhone4卖4999
iPhone 4 sold for 4999

74
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:13,700
iPhone8卖5888
iPhone 8 sold for 5888

75
00:02:13,866 --> 00:02:15,500
iPhone12卖6299
iPhone 12 sold for 6299

76
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:18,466
iPhone15ProMax卖12999
iPhone 15 ProMax sold for 12999

77
00:02:18,866 --> 00:02:20,766
价格曲线一路向上
The price curve just keeps climbing

78
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,800
销量也一路向上
And sales keep climbing too

79
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,000
为什么
Why

80
00:02:24,166 --> 00:02:25,733
因为对一部分人来说
Because for some people

81
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:27,400
手机已经不是手机了
A phone is no longer just a phone

82
00:02:27,566 --> 00:02:28,633
是身份
It's status

83
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:29,866
是品味
It's taste

84
00:02:29,966 --> 00:02:33,166
是我跟别人不一样的那张标签
It's the label that says I'm different from everyone else

85
00:02:33,366 --> 00:02:34,933
凡勃伦自己说过一句话
Veblen himself once said

86
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,566
消费某些商品真正的目的
The real purpose of consuming certain goods

87
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,766
是炫耀有能力消费它们
Is to show off the ability to afford them

88
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:41,466
苹果太懂这个了
Apple understands this perfectly

89
00:02:41,566 --> 00:02:43,366
他们卖的不是性能
They're not selling performance

90
00:02:43,366 --> 00:02:45,066
是我配得上的感觉
They're selling the feeling that I deserve this

91
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,366
你回想一下
Think back

92
00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:48,800
你上次咬牙买Pro的那一秒
The second you grit your teeth and bought the Pro

93
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:51,533
真的是因为120赫兹屏幕吗
Was it really because of the 120Hz screen

94
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:56,000
还是只是不想拿那部看上去就便宜的标准版
Or did you just not want to be seen with the cheap-looking standard model

95
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,866
请你诚实回答自己
Be honest with yourself

96
00:02:58,066 --> 00:03:00,100
我再给你一个更狠的数据
Let me give you an even more brutal stat

97
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:02,166
茅台2024年涨价8%
Maotai raised prices 8% in 2024

98
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,866
销量同比涨14%
Sales jumped 14% year over year

99
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:07,066
爱马仕铂金包2025年涨价12%
Hermes Birkin bag went up 12% in 2025

100
00:03:07,366 --> 00:03:09,166
预约排到2027年
The waitlist extends to 2027

101
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,466
这些品牌的财务报表里
Hidden in these brands' financial reports

102
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,066
藏着同一个逻辑
Is the exact same logic

103
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:15,033
涨价不是为了多赚一点钱
Raising prices isn't about making a bit more money

104
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:17,200
是为了筛掉不够格的客户
It's about filtering out customers who don't qualify

105
00:03:17,366 --> 00:03:18,466
筛掉之后
Once filtered out

106
00:03:18,466 --> 00:03:22,333
剩下的客户更愿意为我跟别人不一样买单
The remaining customers are more willing to pay for being different

107
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,466
苹果在手机行业里
In the phone industry Apple

108
00:03:24,466 --> 00:03:26,266
干的就是同一件事
Is doing the exact same thing

109
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,733
每一次涨价
Every price increase

110
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:30,200
都是一次身份门槛的拉高
Is raising the status barrier another notch

111
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,800
你以为它在涨价
You think they're raising prices

112
00:03:32,066 --> 00:03:34,933
其实它在筛选谁配做苹果用户
They're actually screening who deserves to be an Apple user

113
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,800
注意听
Listen up

114
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:39,100
这里讲一个比凡勃伦效应更狠的招
Here's a trick even more ruthless than the Veblen effect

115
00:03:39,266 --> 00:03:40,600
它叫价格锚定
It's called price anchoring

116
00:03:40,766 --> 00:03:42,066
你去苹果店
You walk into an Apple store

117
00:03:42,066 --> 00:03:44,533
店员第一句话从来不会推标准版
The staff will never lead with the standard model

118
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:46,966
他会先拉你去看ProMax
They'll pull you over to look at the ProMax first

119
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,533
咱们这是顶配
This is our top model

120
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:49,566
1TB
1TB

121
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,166
钛合金边框
Titanium frame

122
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:52,166
13999
13999

123
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,400
你一听
You hear that

124
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:54,633
好贵
So expensive

125
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,100
然后他指向旁边
Then they point to the side

126
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,700
这是Pro
This is the Pro

127
00:03:57,766 --> 00:03:58,866
512G
512G

128
00:03:58,866 --> 00:03:59,933
11499
11499

129
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:01,500
你心里一比
You compare in your head

130
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,500
便宜了2500
2500 cheaper
